ISLAMABAD, Jul 29 (APP):Special Assistant to the Prime Minister (SAPM) on National Health Services, Dr Zafar Mirza on Wednesday submitted his resignation.  In a tweet Mirza said, “I have resigned as SAPM. I came to Pakistan on a personal invitation of Prime Minister Imran Khan leaving WHO.”
He added, “I worked hard and honestly. It was a privilege to serve Pakistan. I am satisfied that I leave at a time when COVID-19 has declined in Pakistan as a result of a grand national effort.”
